queen of pose 🦋

here’s an unsolicited article of my favorite posing tips and tricks I’ve learned: 

•angles! are! everything! think triangles and shapes

•keep moving! movement will help you get more comfortable and also just keep the momentum of posing going 

•stand straight, extend your legs. daddy long legs ftw is all I’m saying. 

•I’m a big advocate of good music, especially if you’re not feeling yourself that day. listen, a little Beyoncé goes a looong way. 

•i think my dance background and my delusion that feeds my confidence, letting me tap into this fierce character that channels Naomi is a huge help, so do what it takes to get past that imposter syndrome!! 

•a wonderful photographer who gets the vibe makes the world of a difference! lots of love to @shannonahlstrandheadshots 📸 📸 📸

#graduation #classof2023 #classof2023🎓 #graduate #cincinnati

@uofcincy dis one is for you 🫶 thanks for everything 🥹 @prezpinto I love you

#graduation #classof2023 #gratitude #collegegrad #graduate

as a graduating art student, our “capstone” is composited of three components: (1) a solo thesis show (2) a gallery exhibition as part of DAAPWORKS, and (3) a written thesis research paper. 

what you see in this is our solo show, which we don’t always get full control of location and space wise, but I was pretty excited to be sharing this space with @pomedraws and @gabrielle.barrera, two artists I look up to immensely.

the process of curating some of my favorite works (and notedly a very small selection of all the works I created the past four years) was a lot of work and lots of prep, trial and error, but it was really therapeutic and cathartic at the end. this work is called “Entering Apotheosis”, alluding to the Greek definition and my interpretation of tapping into one’s highest power and best stage of life, being deified, etc. can you tell I’m obsessed with the Renaissance and art history 🤪 this work is autobiographical and in turn a reclamation 

i had a really hard time feeling like I fit into this major and considered switching majors numerous times (and I also did lol), but I’m really glad I stuck with it! it’s so rewarding, and I’m excited about where my portfolio is going as an all-round artist with my interests so deeply embedded in the entertainment and media industry - be it through photography, directing and curatorial art, acting, modeling, dancing, singing, producing, it’s all VERY interlinked

i graduated a whole year early, and I’m very restless and ready for the next thing, so although I’m eager to move and make a name for myself, I’m not rushing into anything anymore! what’s meant for me (and you) will never pass me (or us)!!! college went by in the blink of an eye

thank you SO much to everyone who came to our reception :’) it meant the world to be celebrating art alongside some of my very favorite people 

#graduation #classof2023 #capstone #thesis #artist #photographer #fineartphotography #fineart #art #daap

The amount of gratitude that I have for everyone I met and everyone that was a part of making this film is insurmountable. I feel like I’ve made lifelong friends with the most incredible energy. Acting is such a beautiful craft and one of the hardest careers, and I am genuinely so happy to have such determined and empowering people by my side.

Fun fact: the day before I traveled for filming, I crashed my car into a mailbox, breakingthe mailbox and my side mirror (justclumsygirltingzyikes), and then I got food poisoning and violently threw up, being nursed by @abbeypmay (God I love this woman) before the first day of filming! A rocky start to one of the most enlightening experiences of my life. 

The most wonderful director, miss @rachelannettehelson is a force to be reckoned with, has the coolest jumpsuits and the cutest iggys. 

I love you!! @angelprater @abbeypmay @itscathymarks @mike_manning_ @nicholasdavidking @sterlingsulieman
